            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685605009725-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1685605009725-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>hoisin sauce </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>,<strong> five-spice mix</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>hoisin stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685605013273-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685605013273-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685605013273-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685605013273-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1685605013273-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion petals are starting to soften, add the<strong> spring onion whites</strong> (save the spring onion greens for garnish!),<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>hoisin stock</strong> to the pan and reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>Mongolian-style lamb stir-fry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685605017758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685605017758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685605017758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685605017758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1685605017758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mongolian-style lamb stir-fry</strong> over the <strong>garlic rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved spring onion greens</strong>, <strong>remaining chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and plenty of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
